The tour will be the first time in 12 years the comedian has performed a live stand-up gig. A source said: "He has lined up venues across the country, including in Manchester, London and Birmingham, and is hoping to announce it in September. "He could not be more ready to get back out there." Kay, 48, stepped back from the public eye in 2017, when he suddenly cancelled his sold-out 14-month Have Gags Will Travel tour. 